---
const spaces = [
  'Space to respond when someone needs help',
  'Space to say yes to unexpected opportunity',
  'Space to weather job loss without panic',
  'Space to give generously when the moment calls',
];
---

<section class="py-24 md:py-36 bg-warm-cream">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <!-- Typography-only opening: the quiet emotional peak -->
      <div class="text-center reveal">
        <p class="font-quote text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-text-deep leading-[1.2] italic">
          "Margin is an act of trust in God."
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Divider -->
      <div class="my-16 flex justify-center reveal">
        <div class="w-16 h-px bg-text-faint/30"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- Section header + content -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 md:gap-12">
        <div class="md:col-span-5 reveal">
          <p class="text-storehouse-600 font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase">
            The deeper meaning
          </p>
          <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl text-text-deep leading-[1.05]">
            Financial peace as an act of worship.
          </h2>
        </div>

        <div class="md:col-span-6 md:col-start-7 reveal reveal-delay-1">
          <p class="text-lg text-text-body leading-relaxed">
            Living below your means creates space for the unpredictable:
          </p>

          <ul class="mt-8 space-y-4">
            {spaces.map((item, i) => (
              <li class="flex items-start gap-4">
                <span class="font-display text-lg text-storehouse-500/60 flex-shrink-0 w-6">
                  {String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}
                </span>
                <span class="text-text-body">{item}</span>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Closing thought -->
      <div class="mt-16 max-w-2xl mx-auto space-y-6 text-lg text-text-body leading-relaxed reveal">
        <p>
          Optimizing every dollar leaves no room for God to move. Building margin says: I trust God enough that I don't need to control everything. I can hold my finances with open hands.
        </p>
        <p class="font-display text-2xl text-text-deep">
          This is worship.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
